docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, Nov. 17. -- Foreign Minister Saavedra Lamas made public today the text of a proposed South American anti-war covenant which Argentina submitted to other South American Foreign Offices in June. Accompanying the text was a long statement explaining its objects and saying the compact already had been accepted by several republics.

docs.snippet: Reflecting the deepening pessimism in the foreign exchange market over the effect upon Great Britain's financs of either a default of cash payment of the December war debt instalment, the pound sterling fell 4 5/8 cents yesterday to $3.20 1/2, the...
docs.lead_paragraph: Reflecting the deepening pessimism in the foreign exchange market over the effect upon Great Britain's financs of either a default of cash payment of the December war debt instalment, the pound sterling fell 4 5/8 cents yesterday to $3.20 1/2, the lowest price since 1920.

headline.main: POUND OFF TO $3.20 1/2 LOWEST SINCE 1920; Uncertainty on Debt Payment Is Blamed for Sharp Net Loss of 4 1/8 Cents for Day. BANKERS ARE PESSIMISTIC Fear Grave Effects From Either Cash or Exchange Plans -- Our Gold Supply Rises.

docs.lead_paragraph: NEW HAVEN, Conn., Nov. 25. -- Officials of the Western Cartridge Company, formerly the Winchester Arms Company, of this city, confirmed tonight reports that an order for cartridges had just been received from a South American country which will keep the factory employed until Christmas.

docs.lead_paragraph: Wall Street professed yesterday to see indications of a "sold-out situation" in the share market. This was assigned as the cause of the firm and steady tone on the Stock Exchange. The volume of trading was smaller than on the previous Saturday, 376,000 shares, compared with 385,556.
